articles.title: Environmental tobacco smoke exposure and pelvic inflammatory disease: a cross-sectional analysis of serum cotinine.
articles.summary:
Here's a clear, concise summary sentence:

Passive cigarette smoke exposure, measured by serum cotinine, was found to be associated with increased risk of pelvic inflammatory disease in non-smoking women.
